---
import '../styles/landing.css';
import '../styles/legal.css';
import CookieBanner from '../components/CookieBanner.astro';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Privacy Policy — Orbiter</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Privacy Policy for orbiter.sh" />
  <meta name="robots" content="noindex" />
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://orbiter.sh/privacy" />
  <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.svg" type="image/svg+xml" />
</head>
<body id="top">

  <nav>
    <a href="/" class="nav-logo">🪐 <span>Orbiter</span></a>
    <div class="nav-links">
      <a href="/">Home</a>
      <a href="https://github.com/aeon022/orbiter">GitHub</a>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <main class="legal-page">
    <div class="legal-header">
      <div class="legal-label">Legal</div>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="legal-meta">Last updated: April 2026 · Applies to orbiter.sh</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-body">

      <h2>1. Controller</h2>
      <p>
        The controller responsible for data processing on this website within the meaning of the GDPR is:
      </p>
      <address>
        Gerwin Weiher<br />
        Abteilung83<br />
        8010 Graz, Austria<br />
        <a href="mailto:post@abteilung83.com">post@abteilung83.com</a><br />
        +43 660 567 23 61
      </address>

      <h2>2. What data we collect</h2>
      <p>
        This website (<strong>orbiter.sh</strong>) is a static informational site. We do not operate any user accounts, comment systems, or contact forms on this domain.
      </p>
      <p>
        When you visit this website, your browser automatically transmits certain technical data to the hosting server:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>IP address (anonymised after processing)</li>
        <li>Date and time of the request</li>
        <li>URL of the requested page</li>
        <li>HTTP status code</li>
        <li>Browser type and version (User-Agent)</li>
        <li>Referring URL</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        This data is processed solely to ensure the technical operation of the website and is not linked to any personal identity. Log files are retained for a maximum of 30 days and then deleted.
      </p>
      <p>Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR (legitimate interest in operating a functional and secure website).</p>

      <h2>3. Cookies and tracking</h2>
      <p>
        This website uses <strong>no tracking cookies</strong>, no analytics services (Google Analytics, Plausible, etc.), and no third-party marketing scripts.
      </p>
      <p>
        The only cookies that may be set are technically necessary session cookies from the hosting infrastructure. These are not used to track or profile you. See our <a href="/cookies">Cookie Policy</a> for details.
      </p>

      <h2>4. External links</h2>
      <p>
        This site contains links to external services (GitHub, npm, Polar.sh, abteilung83.at). When you follow these links you leave our website. We have no control over the data processing practices of these third parties and recommend reading their respective privacy policies.
      </p>
      <p>
        In particular, the <strong>Support Orbiter</strong> link leads to <a href="https://polar.sh" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Polar.sh</a>, an independent payment platform. Any data you provide there is governed by Polar's own privacy policy.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Hosting</h2>
      <p>
        This website is hosted on a third-party infrastructure provider. Server access logs may be generated as described in section 2. The hosting provider acts as a data processor under a data processing agreement with us.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Your rights</h2>
      <p>Under the GDPR you have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Access the personal data we hold about you (Art. 15)</li>
        <li>Rectification of inaccurate data (Art. 16)</li>
        <li>Erasure of your data ("right to be forgotten", Art. 17)</li>
        <li>Restriction of processing (Art. 18)</li>
        <li>Data portability (Art. 20)</li>
        <li>Object to processing (Art. 21)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        To exercise any of these rights, contact us at <a href="mailto:post@abteilung83.com">post@abteilung83.com</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        You also have the right to lodge a complaint with the Austrian Data Protection Authority (<a href="https://www.dsb.gv.at" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">dsb.gv.at</a>).
      </p>

      <h2>7. Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The date at the top of this page reflects the most recent revision.
      </p>

    </div>
  </main>

  <footer>
    <div class="footer-left">
      <span class="footer-logo">🪐 Orbiter</span>
      <span class="footer-meta">MIT License · Built by <a href="https://abteilung83.at">Abteilung83</a></span>
    </div>
    <div class="footer-links">
      <a href="/privacy">Privacy</a>
      <a href="/cookies">Cookies</a>
      <a href="https://abteilung83.at/imprint">Imprint</a>
    </div>
  </footer>

  <CookieBanner />
</body>
</html>
